VeracityDesk The office of Overland Airways at the Murtala Muhammed Airport (MM1) in Lagos, is currently on fire. According to information provided to SaharaReporters by a witness to the tragedy, the fire started at about 10:30a.m; a plane was being serviced at the tarmac when it suddenly went up in flames. “It’s big fire,” the witness told SaharaReporters on phone. “Half of the Overland Airways plane is burnt, while some chartered aircraft being repaired were also torched.” Fire-fighters are currently trying to put out the fire. Details later…